* Added support for specifying `installType` in Android app configurations, allowing administrators to control how an app is deployed to managed devices (e.g. `FORCE_INSTALLED`, `AVAILABLE`, `BLOCKED`). The valid values match the [AMAPI `ApplicationPolicy.InstallType` enum](https://developers.google.com/android/management/reference/rest/v1/enterprises.policies#InstallType). When `installType` is not set, the existing default behavior is preserved (`AVAILABLE` for self-service apps, `PREINSTALLED` for setup-experience apps).
